race.comment: SPIETHTACULAR (11) returned to form last time out when beaten narrowly over this track and trip. Yet to miss the frame in three runs at today's journey. Draws perfectly and looks sure to be in the finish. SAVAGERY VIBE (10) returned from a 24-week spell and was having her first run under Tony Gollan when a game third over 1100m at Ipswich recently. Was competitive in better races than this in Sydney and Melbourne last prep. Stacks of improvement to come. METALCRAFT (12) led all the way for a decisive win over 1100m at Ipswich last start. Up in grade but is a promising three-year-old who has plenty of room for further progress. The lightly raced LARADO (9) justified his short quote when resuming last time. Has loads of upside and must be respected.
